Bottle at brewfellas pub in nicosia. Pours copper/amber with a nice white head. Malty with some caramel notes, a bit sweet but well balanced with some hop bitterness
Bottle at brewfellas pub in nicosia. One of the best european ipas i have tasted so far. Smooth flavours with a very nice hop nose

On draught at brewfellas pub in nicosia. Pours clear with a nice golden colour. Great hop aroma that hits you in the face from the first sip. A lot of citrus with some lemony notes. Medium bodied with a nice balance from the hops and the malts. Very easy drinking with a lot of citrus flavours and a nice, dry, refreshing finish. Overall a great beer!
